Definition Unlikely IJK frame, it is moving through the curve. To descirbe motion of particles travling along the curve T - $\vec{T}$ Unit Tangent Vector. Direction particle is heading. N - $\vec{N}$ Normal Vector. Direction particle is turning. B - $\vec{B}$ Binormal Vector. Direction of particle&rsquo;s twisting How to find TNB $\vec{T}$: Unit Tangent $$ egin{align}&amp;\vec{T}(s) = \vec{r}\prime(s) 	ext{ or } \vec{T}(t) =  rac{\vec{r}\prime(t)}{||\vec{r}\prime(t)||}\end{align}$$ $\vec{N}$: Unit Normal $$ egin{align} &amp;\vec{N}(t) =  rac{\vec{T}\prime(t)}{||\vec{T}\prime(t)||} 
ewline &amp;	ext{Every vector with a constant length is perpendicular to it&rsquo;s Tangent vector} 
ewline &amp;	ext{Proof: Let } \vec{v} 	ext{ have constant length} 
ewline &amp;\vec{v}\cdot\vec{v} = |\vec{v}|^2 = C^2 
ewline &amp;\dfrac{d}{dt}(\vec{v}\cdot\vec{v}) = \dfrac{d}{dt}(C^2) 
ewline &amp;\vec{v}\prime\cdot\vec{v} + \vec{v}\cdot\vec{v}\prime = 2(\vec{v}\prime\cdot\vec{v}) = 0 
ewline &amp;	ext{So } \vec{T}(t) \perp \vec{T}\prime(t) \end{align}$$ $\vec{B}$: Unit Binormal $$\vec{B} = \vec{T} 	imes \vec{N}$$

Derivatives $$ egin{align} f\prime(x) &amp;= \lim_{\Delta x 	o 0} rac{f(x + \Delta x) - f(x)}{\Delta x} 
ewline
ewline \vec{r}\prime(t) &amp;= \lim_{\Delta t 	o 0} rac{\vec{r}(t + \Delta t) - \vec{r}(t)}{\Delta t} 
